&lt;p&gt;Test session details:&lt;br/&gt;
clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4694&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4694&lt;/a&gt; - 5.14.0-570.62.1.el9_6.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
servers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4694&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4694&lt;/a&gt; - 5.14.0-570.62.1_lustre.el9.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; the same issue as the common &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19774&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_428: crash on aarch64 - invoked oom-killer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19774&quot;&gt;LU-19774&lt;/a&gt; OOM &quot;CRASH&quot; on aarch64+64k clients that has been hitting a lot recently.  This session is both on x86_64 clients and the crash is on the OSS, but is the only CRASH failure not on aarch64 clients so it seems fairly uncommon.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, this is running &lt;tt&gt;rolling-downgrade-client2&lt;/tt&gt; with a 2.16.1.2 client2 vs. 2.17.50.28 client1+servers.  While test_428 does not itself run on client2, it is possible there is some fallout from the previous test_413A failure in this session...&lt;/p&gt;







